            "content": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\",\n      \"path\": \"pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/schedule.go\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\",\n      \"path\": \"pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/alert_rule.go\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\",\n      \"path\": \"pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/ticker/ticker.go\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\",\n      \"path\": \"pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/recording_rule.go\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"symbols\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\",\n      \"path\": \"pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/schedule.go\",\n      \"symbol\": \"schedulePeriodic\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\",\n      \"path\": \"pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/schedule.go\",\n      \"symbol\": \"processTick\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\",\n      \"path\": \"pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/schedule.go\",\n      \"symbol\": \"runJobFn\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\",\n      \"path\": \"pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/ticker/ticker.go\",\n      \"symbol\": \"New\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\",\n      \"path\": \"pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/ticker/ticker.go\",\n      \"symbol\": \"run\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\",\n      \"path\": \"pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/alert_rule.go\",\n      \"symbol\": \"Run\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"chain\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\",\n      \"path\": \"pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/schedule.go\",\n      \"symbol\": \"Run\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\",\n      \"path\": \"pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/schedule.go\",\n      \"symbol\": \"schedulePeriodic\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\",\n      \"path\": \"pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/schedule.go\",\n      \"symbol\": \"processTick\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\",\n      \"path\": \"pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/schedule.go\",\n      \"symbol\": \"runJobFn\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"The alerting evaluation scheduler is implemented in pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/schedule.go. The scheduler's main entry point is the Run() method, which creates a ticker via ticker.New() (pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/ticker/ticker.go) that emits periodic ticks at regular intervals. The Run() method then calls schedulePeriodic() to enter the event loop. In schedulePeriodic(), the scheduler waits for ticks from the ticker and for each tick calls processTick() to determine which alert rules should be evaluated. The processTick() function builds a list of rules ready to run and uses buildSequences() to organize them, then calls runSequences() to execute them. The runJobFn() method at line 426-442 is where evaluation cycle overruns are detected. When runJobFn() calls ruleRoutine.Eval(&next.Evaluation), if the evaluation channel already has an unprocessed evaluation (a dropped tick), the method logs a warning: 'Tick dropped because alert rule evaluation is too slow' at line 438 of schedule.go. This warning indicates that the previous evaluation took longer than the time budget allocated by the scheduler's base interval. Individual alert rules implement the Rule interface, with alert rules defined in alert_rule.go and recording rules in recording_rule.go. Each rule's Run() method starts a goroutine that waits on an evaluation channel (evalCh) to receive evaluation signals from the scheduler.\"\n}\n",
